AND now the Nations Genious bends low, to Welcome and to Complement a Heroe who brought her Safety with him; for as well the Nobles, as others, came Crouding in, and only a March was made, and not a War, for thoſe who had boaſted ſuch mighty things before, Fled and Scatter'd at the Martial Noiſe of his Drums and Trumpets; that very Army on which they had ſo much Rely'd, coming in a great meaſure over to him;
and to be brief, he with little o • no Effuſion of Blood, King (Jame •
being retir'd) took a quiet poſſeſſion of the Kingdom, amidſt the Loud Shouts and Acclamations o • the People, being every where Addreſſed, and Congratulated.
